%opening
\title{Script Idea for Twix Commercial}
\author{}
\date{}

\begin{document}


\maketitle

\paragraph{News reporter.}
I'm here asking people around the world which they like better,
Kit-Kat or Twix.

\paragraph{Person.}
I like Twix because it has a cookie in it.

\paragraph{Person.}
I like Twix better because it has everything Kit-Kat has, plus
caramel.

\paragraph{Person.}
Twix, easily.
The Kit-Kat is bland; a tasteless wafer covered in subpar chocolate.
No thank you.

\paragraph{Person.}
I like Twix better.


\paragraph{Twins.}
We like Twix because there is one for each of us.

\paragraph{Goat.}
I'll eat anything.

\paragraph{Person.}
I don't always eat candy bars, but when I do,
I eat Twix.

\paragraph{Person.}
Kit-kats seem to melt much faster.

\paragraph{Astronaut.}
I like Twix because it is out of this world!

\paragraph{Person.}
I. Love. Twix.

\paragraph{News reporter.}
There you have it: Twix is the winner.

\end{document}

